{"/service/ndnp/scu/batch_scu_grapes_ver02/data/sn82004649/00517016482/1923110801/0727.xml":{"full_text":"75 MILLION CAMPAIGN NOTES\nL. H. Miller, Blackville\u2014\u201cI am to pre\nsent the Campaign in person to the church\nes of this division of the Association, and\nassure you that I will do my dead level best\nto put in over in a worthy way. We are\nhaving a good meeting. There have been\n35 additions to date and others are expect\ned before the close Sunday night. The\nmeeting is creating a sentiment that will, I\nfeel, enable us to do the thing more worthi\nly when we do get to it, which will be at\nonce now. I think Blackville can be counted\non to do a worthy thing this year.\u201d\nPastor O. J. Frier: \u201cI preached here\nSunday morning on the appeals that the\nCampaign makes to us at this time, stress\ning especially the moral obligations of our\npledges. One of our large subscribers that\nhadn\u2019t paid any hardly for two years hand\ned the treasurer a check for $600.00 during\nthe week following. We are ali'eady near\nour goal in Denmai'k.\u201d\nPastor W. C. Allen, Dillon: \u201cThe First\nchurch hei\u2019e accepts one-fifth of total pledge\nas a goal and is sti\u2019iving to attain it. Two\nsmall chui\u2019ches I supply in the afternoons\nalso accept this as a goal and both have al\nready paid the one-fifth for this yeai\\\u201d\nOn November 4 there will be three great\ngroup meetings in the interest of the Cam\npaign in the Saluda Association. They are\nas follows: Hopewell, speakei\u2019s, Dr. C. E\nBurts and Dr. W. B. Oliver. Special music\nby Anderson Junior quai'tette. Mt. Bethel,\nDr. John E. White and E. P. Vandiver.\nProspect, speakers. Rev. Eugene R. Pendle\nton, Dr. A. L Smethers.\nOn Sunday, October 28th group meetings\nwere held in the Saluda Association at\nShady Grove, speakers, Dr. C. E. Burts, E.\nP. Vandiver; Cross Roads, speakers, Drs. J,\nM. Burnett and A. L. Smethers; Neals\nCreek, Dr. Jno. E. White, Dr. Thos. J.\nWatts and Foster Brown. These were\ngreat meetings and marked interest was\ndisplayed by large audiences at each place.\nA hopeful spirit prevailed at all the places.\nC. H. Platt, treasurer, Young\u2019s Island:\n\u201cI am working and praying that all pledges\nmay be paid. I would not miss paying\nmine if I had to cut off one meal a day.\u201d\nF. W. Willis, Florence, \u201cWe have just\nbegun to put Florence Association on the\nmap and I am most confident that we shall\nbe able to make a good showing by Decem\nber first.\u201d\nL. H. Raines, Long Creek Academy: \u201cOur\nclerk at the Academy church is sending you\na check today on the Campaign. Am glad\nto report that we were able to go over the\ntop with our pledge.\u201d\nJ. J. Young, Hemingway: \u201cMt. Tabor\nchurch has raised $53.00 for the 75 Million\nCampaign and I will send it to you just as\nsoon as the amount is turned over to me.\u201d\nCarl G. Smith, Westminster: \u201cEvery\nthing is looking favorable in raising our\nquota by December 1st.\u201d\nM. H. Lee, treasurer, Damascus church,\nBattle Creek, S. C.: \u201cWe have been pretty\nquiet but will try letting you begin hearing\nfrom us soon.\u201d\nJno. N. Wrenn, Greenville: \u201cThings look\ngood.\u201d\nDR. GAMBRELL AND HIS CAMPAIGN\nPLEDGE. HE SAID\n\u201cI am going to pay all of it, and more\nif I can, because:\n1. I made it.\n2. It is a covenant between me and my\nGod.\n3. It represents my agreement with my\nbrethren in a great cause.\n4. The great kingdom program, in\nwhich are all interests I love, is involved in\nits payment.\n5. It is right; it is honest.\n6. I want to keep up my re\u2019igious life\nso I can pray and keep fellowship with\nGod.\n7. I want to maintain my self-respect\nso I can keep on good terms with myself.\n8. I will thus help the forces in winning\nsouls, training workers, healing the sick,\ncaring for the orphans, and in bringing in\nthe kingdom of Christ in all the world.\nA LOVER\u2019S WATCH\nPastor Walter R. Alexander tells the\nfollowing bit of romance: \u201cWhen the\npledges were made to the Campaign,\nDecember, 1919, I was sent for by an\nelderly couple in my church at Stam\nford, Texas. They were over seventy\nand were people of very limited means.\nThe lady, her heart set upon making a\npledge but having no money to give, of\nfered her gold watch, the gift of her\nhusband years before. I was deeply\nmoved and refused at first to accept it.\nShe insisted however and her husband\nassured me that he was willing for her\nto give it for they had nothing else to\ngive I was to sell it for the few dol\nlars it might bring and turn the cash\nin toward the 75 'Million Campaign.\nToo much moved for many words, I\nhad prayer with them and left with the\nwatch in my pocket. Fifty years be\nfore a happy lover had given it too his\nbride-to-be. Now I was to sell it for\nthe few paltry dollars that it might\nbring! How could I do it? After sev\neral days of thought and prayer, I mail\ned it to the State Secretary, Dr. F. S.\nGroner, Dallas, giving him all the de\ntails of the story. Lunching one day\nwith one of Dr. Truett\u2019s wealthy lay\nmen Dr. Groner showed the watch and\nretold the story of an aged Christian\u2019s\nlove and sacrifice\u2014a Twentieth Century\nMidow\u2019s Mite. A few days later I re\nceived word that this wealthy layman\nhad bought the watch for $250.00 cash,\nand I will never forget the joy such\nsurprising news gave the dear old lady\nwho had offered it. But the best is yet\nto be. On Christmas morning, just a\nfew weeks later, the dear old soul found\nher watch under her plate at the break\nfast table. Her surprise knew no bounds.\nThe layman had gone to the home of her\nmarried daughter then living in Dallas\nand asked her to see to it that her\nmother received it Christmas day with\nhis best wishes. It was a most unex\npected ending to a story of genuine\nsacrifice. I might add that the knowl\nedge of this sacrificial gift did far more\nthan all my preaching to put my church\nover the top that week of the Cam\npaign.\u201d\nEVERY ASSOCIATION MUST DO ITS\nPART\n$700,000.00 in payments to the Baptist\n75 Million Campaign in November\u2014This\ngoal must be reached.\nWe are looking to every association to\ndo its part\u2014the small associations\u2014the\ngreat associations.\nLook at some of the expectations:\nAbbeville_$ 50,000.00\nAiken_ 18,000.00\nBarnwell___ 38,000.00\nBeaverdam _ 20,000.00\nBroad River_:_ 25,000.00\nReedy River_ 19,000.00\nPee Dee __ 40,000.00\nSaluda_ 78,000.00\nFairfield _ 30,000.00\nGreenville _ 93,000.00\nLaurens_ 60,000.00\nAll other associations would show in like\nproportion. A big challenge this to our\nconservation, to our zeal and to our fidelity\nto our stewardship obligations.\nSOUTH CAROLINA BAPTIST LAYMEN\u2019S\nORGANIZATION\nBaptist Laymen of South Carolina:\nWe are nearing the end of the fourth\nyear of our great Campaign. December\nthe first will bring us to the end and the\nfourth year will have been finished.\nTo finish it in a worthy manner depends\nupon the splendid body of our Baptist lay\nmen. It is for them to write victory or de\nfeat.\nThe Baptists of South Carolina have\nraised three million two hundred and fifty\nthousand dollars, which is two million three\nhundred thousand dollars more than in any\nlike period before the present plan was\nadopted and the Seventy-Five Million Cam\npaign inaugurated. All of our denomina\ntional enterprises have received more ade\nquate support than ever before. But for\nthis timely and generous support many of\nour institutions and churches would have\nsuffered serious financial embarrassment.\nThese great things could not have been\naccomplished during the financial depres\nsion through which our people have passed\nbut for the courageous and sacrificial\nspirit of many of the laymen. The achieve\nments of the past, the urgent need of the\npresent, the return of prosperity to our peo\nple, are a positive challenge to the Baptist\nlaymen of South Carolina. A challenge to\ntheir loyalty, to their faith, to their devo\ntion to duty, and to their sense of responsi\nbility. In this hour of supreme need every\nBaptist layman\u2014rich and poor\u2014should\nanswer this challenge in the spirit of Chris\ntian stewardship.\nBecause of the gravity of the situation,\nand the immediate need for prompt and\nefficient action, I am making this second\nappeal, asking that you cooperate with\nyour church committee and help to create\na spirit of confidence and enthusiasm.\nIf every man goes forward with the con\nscientious determination to do his full duty,\nthe task will be accomplished and the vic\ntory won.\nFraternally yours,\nI. H. Hunt, Chairman\nNewberry, S. C.,\nNovember 1, 1923.","height":"17600","width":"13820"}}
